00484 /* BCC - Test if the file exists - 7/14/97 */
00485 static int
00486 lexExist (char *file_name, int inclusion)
00487 {
00488   FILE *fpt;
00489   char *last_file;
00490 
00491   last_file = current_file;
00492   /*
00493    *      If the current_file is specified from the
00494    *      root directory, do nothing.
00495    *      Otherwise, add the prefix of the last file
00496    *      to the front of the file_name.
00497    */
00498   if (inclusion && (file_name[0] != '/'))
00499     {
00500       int len, j, i;
00501       char temp1[1024];
00502       len = strlen (last_file);
00503       /* find the prefix: /x/y/z -> /x/y */
00504       for (i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--)
00505         if (last_file[i] == '/')
00506           break;
00507       for (j = 0; j <= i; j++)
00508         temp1[j] = last_file[j];
00509       for (i = 0; i <= strlen (file_name); i++)
00510         temp1[i + j] = file_name[i];
00511       file_name = FindString (temp1);
00512     }
00513 
00514   if (!strcmp (file_name, "stdin"))
00515     {
00516       return 1;
00517     }
00518   else
00519     {                           /* open new file */
00520       fpt = fopen (file_name, "r");
00521       if (fpt == NULL)
00522         {
00523           return 0;
00524         }
00525       return 1;
00526     }
00527 }

00623 /* Process an integer Literal */
00624 #ifdef __linux__
00625 /* ADA: 7/9/96: Linux libc atoi() will return MAX_LONG if input string is too
00626         large.  This is disastrous when reading a huge number still in unsigned
00627         long range.  Use the following routine instead.  Different name is used
00628         to avoid conflict with linux header files */
00629 static int
00630 atoi_linux (char *s)
00631 {
00632   /* 
00633    * atoi() exsits to allow overflow int in s
00634    */
00635   char *p = s;
00636   int neg, ret;
00637 
00638   if ((p = s) == NULL)
00639     return 0;
00640 
00641   while (isspace (*p))
00642     p++;
00643 
00644   if (*p == '-')
00645     {
00646       p++;
00647       neg = 1;
00648     }
00649   else if (*p == '+')
00650     {
00651       p++;
00652       neg = 0;
00653     }
00654   else
00655     {
00656       neg = 0;
00657     }
00658 
00659   for (ret = 0; *p; p++)
00660     if (isdigit (*p))
00661       {
00662         ret *= 10;
00663         ret += *p - '0';
00664       }
00665     else
00666       {
00667         break;
00668       }
00669 
00670   return (neg) ? -ret : ret;
00671 }
00672 #endif

00751 /*      Find a string.  */
00752 static String *
00753 FindS (String * T, char *str)
00754 {
00755   int diff;
00756 
00757   if (T == 0)                   /* not found */
00758     return 0;
00759   diff = strcmp (str, T->name);
00760   if (diff == 0)
00761     return (T);                 /* find a match */
00762   if (diff > 0)
00763     return (FindS (T->left, str));      /* search left */
00764   else
00765     return (FindS (T->right, str));     /* search right */
00766 }
00767 
00768 /*      Add a string.   */
00769 static String *
00770 AddS (String * T, char *str)
00771 {
00772   int diff;
00773   String *new_str;
00774 
00775   if (T == 0)
00776     {                           /* add new string */
00777       new_str = (String *) lmalloc (sizeof (String));
00778       new_str->name = strsave (str);
00779       new_str->left = new_str->right = 0;
00780       return (new_str);
00781     }
00782   diff = strcmp (str, T->name);
00783   if (diff == 0)
00784     return (T);                 /* already exist */
00785   if (diff > 0)
00786     {
00787       T->left = AddS (T->left, str);    /* add to left */
00788       return (T);
00789     }
00790   else
00791     {
00792       T->right = AddS (T->right, str);  /* add to right */
00793       return (T);
00794     }
00795 }

00932 /*
00933  *      Get a node or a complete list from input.
00934  *      It is assumed that the lexer has been properly set up.
00935  */
00936 LIST GetNode (void)
00937 {
00938   int node_type;
00939   LIST new_node, ptr;
00940 
00941   node_type = yylex ();         /* get token */
00942 
00943   if (node_type == 0)
00944     {                           /* end of file */
00945       new_node = NewNode ();
00946       NodeType (new_node) = T_EOF;
00947       return new_node;
00948     }
00949 
00950   switch (node_type)
00951     {
00952     case L_ID:                  /* identifier */
00953       new_node = NewNode ();
00954       NodeType (new_node) = T_ID;
00955       StringOf (new_node) = FindString (TokenName);
00956       break;
00957     case L_INT:         /* integer */
00958       new_node = NewNode ();
00959       NodeType (new_node) = T_INT;
00960       ScalarOf (new_node) = TokenInteger;
00961       break;
00962     case L_REAL:                /* real constant literal */
00963       new_node = NewNode ();
00964       NodeType (new_node) = T_REAL;
00965       RealOf (new_node) = TokenReal;
00966       break;
00967     case L_STRING:              /* string literal */
00968       new_node = NewNode ();
00969       NodeType (new_node) = T_STRING;
00970       StringOf (new_node) = FindString (TokenName);
00971       break;
00972     case L_CHAR:                /* character literal */
00973       new_node = NewNode ();
00974       NodeType (new_node) = T_CHAR;
00975       StringOf (new_node) = FindString (TokenName);
00976       break;
00977     case L_ERROR:               /* erroneous input */
00978       new_node = NewNode ();
00979       NodeType (new_node) = T_NULL;
00980       break;
00981     default:                    /* single character operator */
00982       if (node_type == '(')
00983         {
00984           new_node = NewNode ();
00985           NodeType (new_node) = T_LIST;
00986           ChildOf (new_node) = 0;
00987           while ((ptr = GetNode ()) != 0)
00988             AddChildNode (new_node, ptr);
00989         }
00990       else if (node_type == ')')
00991         {
00992           new_node = 0;
00993         }
00994       else
00995         {
00996           char line[10];
00997           sprintf (line, "'%c'", node_type);
00998           new_node = NewNode ();
00999           NodeType (new_node) = T_CHAR;
01000           StringOf (new_node) = FindString (line);
01001         }
01002       break;
01003     }
01004   return new_node;
01005 }
